      "side": 1,
      "message": "Of course. Here\u0027s what I do\n\n1. Build bbagent binary on your local workstation against the targeted plaform.\n2. use `led get-builder ... | led edit-isolated  \u003e out.json` to isolate the bbagent binary.\n3. Delete bbagent from `cipd_packages` list in out.json so that swarming won\u0027t download that from cipd\n4. led launch\n\n\nAlso, I think `edit-isolated` is mutually exclusive with `edit-recipe-bundle`. If you want to test a recipe change at the same time, you need to use `led edit-isolated` and manually bundle the recipe (i.e. `./recipes.py bundle --destination XXX`) to the `kitchen-checkout` subdir of the tmp isolate dir.",
      "parentUuid": "94069ab1_457ad08f",
      "revId": "ac6c9cfdc33fe0da9cc09f6664491cad2533efb5",
